Reedy Creek Observatory is the location for observations of near-Earth objects by John Broughton, an Australian astronomer.
The International Astronomical Union (IAU) observatory code for Reedy Creek is 428.
The observatory is located on the Gold Coast, Queensland at Reedy Creek, Queensland, a suburb with post code 4228 and located at 28°06′S 153°24′E.
Broughton gives the location of his observatory [1] as Longitude (East +ve): +153 23' 49" Latitude (South -ve): -28 06' 36" Height above Sea level: 66 metres


